sec.p:
The importance of the ingredients and method of processing can be revealed by considering the primary requirements for solid rocket motor insulation:


excellent bonding of the insulator with propellant and motor case over the entire range of working temperature;

low ablation rate (from 0.09 to 0.2 mm/s);

low density (from 1.05 to 1.5 gm/cm3);

sufficient tensile strength (≥0.5 MPa);

low thermal conductivity (from 0.2 to 0.5 W/m-K);

high specific heat (from 1000 to 2100 J/kg-K);

porous char with good retention characteristics;

ability to withstand mechanical and thermal stresses during storage, handling, and curing operations;

low moisture absorption;

good aging characteristics (minimum 10 years of shelf/useful life);

very low outer case temperature (<150°C) over the entire range of working temperature; and

good electrical conductivity (to avoid accumulation of static electricity).
